Caribbean\u2014spaces that defy static categorization, existing instead as boundless and expansive spaces, in a perpetual state of flux, between land and sea. \n\nFocusing in particular on the intersections of these locales as \u201cplaces of exchange,\u201d Tulloch draws inspiration from creolization, using it as a lens to develop a visual language that expresses the blending of African,
